# Code Organization Rules

## File Size Limit
- Maximum 120 lines per file
- If a file exceeds 120 lines, refactor into smaller components/modules
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks
- Extract shared UI into component library

## Component Structure
- One component per file
- Co-locate related files in feature folders
- Use composition over large monolithic components
- Separate concerns: types, hooks, components, utils

## Best Practices
- Custom hooks for state management and business logic
- Shared components for reusable UI patterns
- Feature folders for related functionality
- Clear, focused file responsibilities
